  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The maximum of the occurrences (i.e., distribution frequencies) for all three algorithms at around 3 log a.u.",
    "can be interpreted as an upper bound for peak amplitudes resulting from background noise (Rydelek and Sacks, 1989).",
    "After that threshold, RECmax does not tend to find larger-amplitude events.",
    "In contrast, RECmin and multi-STA/LTA preferentially detect those events.",
    "The variegated structure of the curves for both algorithms indicates composition by mixed populations of event types."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "can be interpreted as an upper bound for peak amplitudes resulting from background noise (Rydelek and Sacks, 1989)."
  ]
}